name: GuildsCollection
description: The guilds collection class. This is not the collection of guilds but the collection of the {Guilds} object. This is used for caching.

name: fetch
description: Fetches user's guilds and updates the cache.

params.description: The user key of the user whose guilds are to be fetched.
params.name: key

params.description: If true, fetches guilds from the discord API, if set to false, fetches from the cache instead.
params.name: refresh

examples: let myFavGuilds = myGuildCollection.fetch('my-fav-user\'s key'); // Gets from the collection if available.
let myFavGuilds = myGuildCollection.fetch('my-fav-user\'s key', true); // Gets from discord API only.

returns.description: The guilds of the user whose user key was provided.

params.description: Same as a normal collection's parameters.
params.name: params
